Short Description:
Łódzki Dom Kultury( so called ŁDK | Lodzkie  is one of the oldest culture institutions in Łódź Voivodeship - it exists since 1953. Every year it organises and co-organises festivals, concerts, exhibitions, reviews and other cultural activities which attract thousands of people. Łódzki Dom Kultury plays an important role in the region - not only by organising and co-organising cultural events in the whole Łódź Voivodeship but as well by providing professional trainings for culture sector staff, helping to improve their skills in culture management. 

Łódzki Dom Kultury:
- over 1000 screenings per year, film reviews and festivals, 2 cinemas;
- around 100 exhibitions per year, 5 art galleries;
- over 150 events per year (including concerts, meetings, lectures et cetera);
- clubs, associations, foundations, music band, theatre groups;
-  various courses (including dancing, yoga, drawing, painting et cetera);
- Regional Academy of Culture Sector (trainings, courses, workshops improving culture management skills);
- culture information website Kalejdoskop Kulturalny Reymont (http://www.e-kalejdoskop.pl);
- culture information website for the whole Łódź Voivodeship (http://www.RegionKultury.pl),
- "Kalejdoskop" - magazine dedicated to culture issues;
- "Kwadratura" - publishing house dedicated to poetry.
